Flex Box :
-> it is short form of flexible-box
-> it is one- directional
-> by default flex-box is responsive
1. display-flex;
2. justify-content : flex-start, flex-end, space-evenly;
3. align-items: flex-start, flex-end, center, stretch;
4. gap - it defines the gap between the html elements
Ex : gap : 20px;
5. flex- direction: row, column, row-reverse, column
6. order - it specifies the order of the html elements
7. flex- grow - it defines the expansion proportion of particular element 
->by default it is 0
8. flex- shrink - it defines the collapsion/compression of 
-> default value is 1
9. flex-basis - it defines the initial size of the elements
->default value is auto
Program :
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head> 
        <title>flexbox</title>
        <style>
            .parent{
                width: 100%;
                height: 100vh;
                display: flex;
                /*justify-content: flex-start;
                flex-wrap: nowrap;
                flex-direction: column-reverse; 
                order: 1; */
                
            }
            .child{
                height: 200px;
                width: 400px;
                border: 1px solid black;
                background-color: yellow;
            }
            .c1{
                background-color: blue;
                /*flex-grow: 3;
                flex-shrink: 2; */
                flex-basis: 30%;
            }
            .c2{
                background-color: red;
                
            }
            .c3{
                background-color: green;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="parent">
            <div class="child c1">1</div>
            <div class="child c2">2</div>
            <div class="child c3">3</div>
        </div>
        <div class="parent">
            <div class="child c1">1</div>
            <div class="child c2">2</div>
            <div class="child c3">3</div>
        </div>
        <div class="parent">
            <div class="child c1">1</div>
            <div class="child c2">2</div>
            <div class="child c3">3</div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
